<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 2:53PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Las Marias, Anasco,
Mayaguez, San Sebastian, Rincon, Moca and Aguada Municipalities
through 245 PM AST...
At 152 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was over Anasco, moving west at
10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 30 mph, pea sized hail, frequent lightning and
heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Aguada, Rincon, Las Marias, San Sebastian, Anasco, La Playa, Hato
Arriba, Luyando, Espino and Stella.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
